Mayor of Lisbon Carlos Moedas speaks at the opening ceremony of the Web Summit 2021 in Lisbon, Portugal, Nov. 1, 2021. The opening of the Web Summit on Monday night in Lisbon marked the post-pandemic resumption of one of the biggest events worldwide in the field of technology and innovation. (Photo by Pedro Fiuza/Xinhua) LISBON, Nov. 1 (Xinhua) -- The opening of the Web Summit on Monday night in Lisbon marked the post-pandemic resumption of one of the biggest events worldwide in the field of technology and innovation. With the presence of about 40,000 visitors, the Web Summit 2021 is joined by more than 700 speakers from technology and Internet companies. This year's edition brings together technology experts and investors, as well as some social activists. Carlos Moedas, mayor of Lisbon, promised to create a "Unicorns Factory" in the Portuguese capital next year. "This is where people who love details come together. If you think about innovation -- my dream is that Lisbon will be the innovation capital of the world," he said. The in-person Web Summit will run till Thursday. Enditem  